The National Civil Society Congress, Ncsc, Under The Umbrella Of The Referendum Debate Platform (REDEP), Are Calling Upon The Government To Put In Place A Civic Education Programme Ahead Of A Potential Change In The Constitution, Which Might Take Place After The BBI REPORT Has Been Presented. NCSC Now Says Since The Constitution Was Passed By More Than 67% Of Voters In 2010, Therefore, Any Attempts To Amend It Must Fully Involve Kenyans And Not Just The Political Elite.